SIMPLE: petrifaction
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Petrifaction
<hw>Pet`ri*fac"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Petrify</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The process of petrifying, or
changing into stone; conversion of any organic matter (animal or
vegetable) into stone, or a substance of stony hardness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state or condition of being petrified.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which is petrified; popularly, a body incrusted
with stony matter; an incrustation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Fig.: Hardness; callousness; obduracy.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Petrifaction</xex> of the soul.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Cudworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Petrifactive</ent>⟦br⟧
